cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CL 

The paper deals with the classification of satellite image time series using neural architectures. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of self-attention for temporal feature extraction suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Lastly, the release of an annotated dataset for benchmarking purposes indicates a potential connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
